Finance Agreement :Implementation Agreement between CRG and CPM. Loan Agreement Sched. 2-Sec I-B-2 | Description :The Borrowershall cause the Region of Cusco, acting through PER Plan COPESCO, and for the purposes of assisting in the carrying out of theProject and to formalize their respective responsibilities under the Project to, not later than 30 days after the EffectivenessDate, enter into an agreement with CPM under terms and conditions satisfactory to the Bank (“Implementation Agreement”). | Due Date:01-Jul-2014

Finance Agreement :Implementation in accord/compl with ESIA and Reset. Plan. LA Sched. 2-Sec-I-E-2 | Description :After thecompletion of the final detailed designs mentioned in Component 1(a) (i) of the Project (as described in the Loan Agreement), butprior to the commencement of the civil works under Component 1 (a) (ii) of the Project, the Borrower shall cause the RegionalGovernment of Cusco, acting through PER Plan COPESCO, to ensure that: As stated in Loan Agreement, Schedule 2, Section I-E-2. | DueDate :01-Jun-2015

title.narrative: Strategy to advance pilot projects for public transport service improvement in Cusco is elaborated
1. Average travel time savings in the east-west corridor of Cusco Provincial Municipality (San Jeronimo District – Cusco District)
2. Change in accessibility to employment opportunities by public transport in the area of influence of the east-west corridor of Cusco Provincial Municipality (San Jeronimo District – Cusco District)
Staff trained at PER Plan COPESCO in project management, monitoring and evaluation, and other project implementation capabilities
Cusco Bicycle and Pedestrian Strategy designed and promoted
Proposal for the Mobility and Public Spaces Plan of Cusco elaborated
3. User satisfaction with Via Expresa Avenue
4. Design and execution of Via Expresa Avenue works are informed with at least three audits and/or road safety inspections
